>> A model that is better is the one that is _________.<<

( ) more accurate {{ A more accurate model might be better for certain use cases, but it might not be for others.}}
( ) lightweight {{ A lightweight model might be better for certain use cases, but it might not be for others.}}
( ) fast {{ A fast model might be better for certain use cases, but it might not be for others.}}
( ) All of the above {{ This model might be better for certain use cases, but it might not be for others.}}
(x) None of the above {{What makes a model "better" will depend on the specific use case. For example, a model that is lightweight, fast and more accurate may not be adaptable, making its application range very narrow. If the use case requires a very versatile model, then this model won't be considered "better", no matter how accurate, fast and lightweight it is.}}
